From 4b7c3af1fc886c8fbef9f5176dd62126dfac9138 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: melnoff <melnoff360@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 14:46:18 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ui): subscription sidecar visibility + manual stop/apply
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Patch 14 — addresses 'no idea what subscription proxy is doing' by
splitting the workflow into observable steps and surfacing sidecar
state both in the edit dialog and in the proxy list row.

  * VlessBridge: socksEndpointForSubscription(key) accessor returning
    the local SOCKS5 endpoint of a running subscription sidecar.
  * SubscriptionMonitor gains a sidecarRunning flag (true on actual
    Clash poll, false on idle sentinels) and an endpoint() getter.
  * SubscriptionMonitorRegistry (new) — process-wide singleton
    keyed by subscription URL. Hands out an rpl producer per URL
    that fires status updates whenever the monitor polls or when
    sidecar state changes. notifySidecarChanged() is called from
    the dialog's Stop / Apply buttons so subscribers see "now idle"
    without polling delay.
  * ProxyBox edit dialog:
    - 'Refresh subscription' now only fetches + caches; it no longer
      kills the running sidecar so an active connection is preserved.
    - New 'Apply (restart sidecar)' button — explicit way to push
      a freshly fetched server list to a live sidecar (stops it,
      next forUse() restarts with the new outbounds).
    - New 'Stop sidecar' button for forced shutdown when something
      is wrong.
    - New 'Sidecar: idle / running on 127.0.0.1:NNN · active: vN /
      clash error: ...' status line.
    - On dialog open with an empty cache, auto-fires Refresh so
      the user sees servers without an extra click.
    - Per-dialog SubscriptionMonitor replaced by registry subscription;
      multiple consumers of the same URL now share a single poller.
  * ProxiesBoxController: subscribes per VlessSubscription item to
    the registry, caches sidecarRunning + activeTag + error on the
    Item, and rewrites the row label so the second line reads
    'active: <server-name>' / 'sidecar running, N server(s)' /
    'N server(s) cached' / '(no cache — open & refresh)' instead of
    the unreadable subscription URL.
